remark.code:
With MyStrings do
  try
    BeginUpdate;
    // Some lengthy operation.
  Finally
    EndUpdate
  end;

With MyStrings do
  begin
  Clear;
  Add('String 0');
  Add('String 1');
  Add('String 2');
  Add('String 3');
  Add('String 4');
  Move(1,3);
  end;

descr.remark:
Exchange will not check whether the list os sorted or not; 
if Exchange is called on a sorted list and the strings are not
identical, the sort order of the list will be destroyed.

element.descr:
SkipValue should be used when skipping a value in the stream;
The method should determine the type of the value which should be skipped
by itself, if this is necessary.

descr.p:
An application programmer should not call Destroy directly;
Instead Free should be called, if it needs to be called at all.
Normally the controlling class (e.g. a TActionList) will destroy the action.
